ce:section.ce:para:
The synthesis of GQDs was conducted through chemical oxidation of carbon black in nitric acid by a one-step method [38,39]. The UV–Vis absorption spectrum of GQDs (Fig. 1
                        ) showed a typical absorption band centered at 300 nm, which corresponds to n → π* transition of C = O [45]. When excited at 328 nm, a bright fluorescence emission peaked at 520 nm was observed. The photograph in Fig. 1 elucidated that GQDs had great water-solubility and strong green fluorescence. In addition, GQDs were characterized by HRTEM on different scales, which showed a diameter ranging from 1.0 to 4.0 nm (Fig. 2
                        ), similar to the previous reports. It is worth noting that GQDs are not spherical particles, the AFM scan result reported in the previously published paper showed that they are planar nanocrystals with < 0.8 nm thickness, similar as the graphene material with a single carbon layer [46].
